notesStmt.note: Persian customs stamps solar dated 1312 A.H. (f. 1r, 135v). Owner's note with stamp dated 1281 A.H. (1864 CE)

msContents.summary: Two texts on calendars copied together in the same hand. The first is a commentary on al-Birjandī's Bīst bāb dar taqvīm, followed by a copy of Dar maʻrifat-i taqvīm mushtamil bar sī faṣl by al-Ṭūsī.

supportDesc.extent: 112 unfoliated leaves : 215 x 150 (160 x 90) mm, bound to 215 x 150 mm

layoutDesc.layout: Chiefly written in 19 long lines; some marginalia.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq influenced naskh in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Tables and diagrams in red and black; overlinining in red.

origin.p: Copy completed in 1244 AH (1828 CE) by Sayyid ʻAbd al-Taqī ibn Mīrzā ʻAbd al-Samīʻ al-Ḥusaynī al-Mūsavī al-Shīrāzī (f. 111r, 135r).
